text: The Dumbarton Bridge is the southernmost of the highway bridges across San Francisco Bay in California. It can carry over 70,000 vehicles and about 118 pedestrian and bicycle crossings daily. It is the shortest bridge across San Francisco Bay at . The bridge goes from Menlo Park in the west to Fremont in the east. ==References== Category:1927 establishments in the United States Category:Bridges in the San Francisco Bay Area Category:Steel bridges
